{"id": "EUVD-2022-54561", "enisaUuid": "0292c205-b32f-3884-b808-5440076c789b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: tun: unlink NAPI from device on destruction\n\nSyzbot found a race between tun file and device destruction.\nNAPIs live in struct tun_file which can get destroyed before\nthe netdev so we have to del them explicitly. The current\ncode is missing deleting the NAPI if the queue was detached\nfirst.", "datePublished": "2025-10-24T18:30:56", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-24T18:30:56", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/82e729aee59acefe135fceffadcbc5b86dd4f1b9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a8cf919022373c97a84fe596bbea544f909c485d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bec1be0a745ab420718217e3e0d9542a75108989", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8145f77d38de4f88b8a69e1463f5c09ba189d77c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8661d4b8faa2f7ee7a559969c0a7c57f077b1728", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3b9bc84d311104906d2b4995a9a02d7b7ddab2db", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49672"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49672"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "04047ec3-229f-309e-9bed-d57258a688d2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.53"}, {"id": "27b3f348-b7db-3ef5-bca7-12d600eb3070", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "943170998b200190f99d3fe7e771437e2c51f319 <3b9bc84d311104906d2b4995a9a02d7b7ddab2db"}, {"id": "62074871-0126-37cf-b3f5-fb4ac2fbb9d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "6d0dffa9-69ce-3c7f-91c0-b956bcbdfa5c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "943170998b200190f99d3fe7e771437e2c51f319 <a8cf919022373c97a84fe596bbea544f909c485d"}, {"id": "6d341a93-7f6a-318d-9356-30bea416f05f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "943170998b200190f99d3fe7e771437e2c51f319 <82e729aee59acefe135fceffadcbc5b86dd4f1b9"}, {"id": "879eda17-2453-323f-8f0a-8e8bd97a321c", "p